description: The New Saints beat Europa FC in extra-time to overturn a first-leg deficit and reach the Champions League second qualifying round.
title: Europa 1-3 The New Saints (agg: 3-4)
title_page: Europa 1-3 The New Saints (agg: 3-4) - BBC Sport
maintext:
The New Saints beat nine-man Europa FC in extra-time to overturn a first-leg deficit and reach the second qualifying round of the Champions League.
Trailing 2-1 going into the second leg, the Welsh champions went in front through Ivan Moya's own goal and Scott Quigley's effort on 41 minutes.
The Gibraltar team levelled the tie through Liam Walker's penalty but had Kike Gomez and Alex Quillo sent off.
And Quigley drilled in a low finish on 104 minutes to send TNS through.
They will face Croatian side Rijeka in the next round.
